5:
Are you sure this is the correct
place, Stella? I feel like we discussed
a different location.
11:
According to your original plan, the
spot was supposed to be
somewhere along a Guild Knight
patrol route...
13:
But here, we're within easy reach of
every adventurer thirsting for
something to do—good timing,
given that the Guild isn't offering
their usual quests today.
18:
Not offering quests?
You don't mean...
22:
You don't get ahead in the Guild by
shutting down business, but that
Lilie went and did it for us anyway.
She's quite something.
25:
You guys were planning to do all the
dirty work yourselves, weren't you?
28:
Sometime's it's okay to use other
people to your advantage, you know.
31: You might have a point there.
35:
We will do that, starting from next
time.
44: Are you afraid of what's to come?
49:
I... didn't know.
I had no idea what I was doing.
52:
I kept repeating the same
mistakes...
Over and over...
55: This, too, might be a mistake...
59:
You took up that sword and came
this far... All you need is to take one
more step further.
61:
I know the path forward may be
fraught with dangers... And that you
may be on the verge of losing heart.
63:
But I also know that the very
moment you hear a voice call out
from beyond the darkness, you will
move to help them.
66:
When that time comes, you want to
be ready—armed with knowledge
and strength.
69:
You want to do your best for these
people—just the way Alk does. Isn't
that right?
75:
Yes.
I... don't want to leave anyone
behind. Not again.
80:
So long as that purity of heart
continues to drive you forward, I will
always be by your side, Stella.
83:
If you make a mistake, then I shall
share the responsibility with you. We
go together.
93:
There's still more of them! They're
getting through!
101:
We speak with the authority of the
Stars.
104:
Judgment has been passed.
You have violated the celestial
order.
You are not worthy to stand in the
light.
106:
Fade away, into darkness.
Commencing purge.
114:
Leave this to us. You must go and
see the plan realized!
117:
Don't worry, we'll have time to kick
Purger ass later! Do what you gotta
do, partner.
126:
Violated the celestial order? Not
worthy? Give me a break...
128:
Just who do they think they are,
deciding who lives and who dies?
What gives them the right to call
themselves "Overlords"?
131:
And we're just supposed to sit here
and accept their "judgment"? No
way!
154: Well, that was certainly a close call.
158:
Zekhel? H-how did you even do
that?!
162:
What, you thought I got the job of
captain just 'cause of my stunning
good looks?
165:
Seems we've got more company.
When it rains it pours...
170:
Oh well—time to get to work.
Guild Knights, prepare yourselves!
175:
Load your next rounds!
Cannons at the ready—FIRE!
179:
That's them all right! Those are
EXACTLY the flying golems the
emergency quest described!
183:
By the way, we're offering a special
bonus for reports on their
movement and attack patterns!
Help out in any way you can!
191:
Of course they did. And now that
they're here, it'd be a waste if we
didn't put them to work!
194:
Since I have a feeling you and I are
about to have our hands full.
197:
We speak with the authority of the
Stars.
201:
Yeah, yeah, we heard that one
before. Either get some new
material, or shut the hell up.
210:
My comrades have all been
rescued. I have come to thank you
personally, Hero of the Red Soup!
216:
I can hear them now—my people
are out there, fighting! Their courage
fills me with the determination to
fight!
219:
For I am a warrior. I am the blade of
the Vesta, from now until my dying
day!
228: We'll NEVER lose to the likes of you!
